---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Privacy Policy — Central Communications Ltd" description="Central Communications Ltd privacy policy covering data collection, use and security." noindex={true}>
  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section-tag">Legal</span>
      <h1 class="page-title"><em>Privacy</em> Policy</h1>
      <p class="page-sub">Central Communications Limited</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:820px;">
      <div class="prose">
        <h2>Introduction</h2>
        <p>Central Communications Limited are committed to protecting your privacy as an Internet user whenever you buy goods or services from us. Central Communications will generally be using Direct Payment Solutions Limited (DPS) when the cardholder is using a credit or debit card over the Internet, Phone, Fax, Unattended or Integrated EFTPOS system.</p>
        <p>Central Communications recognizes its responsibility to keep confidential at all times any information which Central Communications acquires in connection with such a transaction, whether directly from the Cardholder or via our website. Central Communications protects personal information (at a minimum) to the Payment Card Industry Data Security Standards (PCI DSS).</p>
        <h2>Collection of Information</h2>
        <p>To enable Central Communications to provide secure payment facilities it will typically request DPS to acquire information which may include the Cardholder's name, credit card number (with the expiry date) and billing address. Central Communications also collects personal information such as name and address for the purpose of creating and maintaining customer accounts.</p>
        <h2>Use and Disclosure of Information</h2>
        <p>DPS uses the information to obtain authorization of the transaction from the Issuing bank of the credit card and to process the payment. Personal customer information will only be used and/or disclosed to trusted third parties if required by Law, or to carry out Central Communications's daily business such as debt collection and customer notifications.</p>
        <h2>Security</h2>
        <p>Central Communications uses a variety of technologies and procedures to help protect personal information from unauthorized access, use or disclosure. When Central Communications transmits sensitive information it protects it through the use of encryption, such as the Secure Socket Layer (SSL) protocol.</p>
        <h2>PCI-DSS</h2>
        <p>PCI-DSS (Payment Card Industry Data Security Standard) is a set of security requirements relating to the protection of card holder data. Central Communications complies with current PCI-DSS standards for any card payment processing.</p>
        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>If you have any questions about this privacy policy, please <a href="/support.html#contact">contact us</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
<style>
  .page-title { font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem); color: #e8f1ff; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem; }
  .page-title em { font-style: normal; color: #0ea5e9; }
  .page-sub { font-size: 1.1rem; color: #7ea3c8; }
</style>
